{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871764863,"sessionID":"ses_285cc1a8cffeXRF2B06zSdTSmn","part":{"id":"prt_d7a34a95b001UJt4Co2mlxqcon","messageID":"msg_d7a34a08c001m3qa5SJYXs5La9","sessionID":"ses_285cc1a8cffeXRF2B06zSdTSmn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-b0ef3badeaf04705baed264f105baecc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装 Implementation Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n4: **Language**: Python\n5: **Size**: M\n6: **Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n7: \n8: ## Task Breakdown\n9: \n10: ### Task 1: Verify DockerService class structure and initialization\n11: - [ ] Verify DockerService class exists in agentcube/services/docker_service.py\n12: - [ ] Verify __init__ method with verbose parameter\n13: - [ ] Verify verbose flag is stored as instance variable\n14: - [ ] Verify logging configuration based on verbose flag\n15: - [ ] Verify lazy initialization of _client property\n16: - [ ] Verify class docstring describes functionality\n17: - [ ] Verify imports are correct (docker, logging, time, pathlib, typing)\n18: \n19: **Verification**: Run `python -c \"from agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService; s = DockerService(verbose=True); print(s)\"` and verify it instantiates correctly\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ### Task 2: Verify Docker availability checking method\n24: - [ ] Verify check_docker_available method exists\n25: - [ ] Verify method calls self.client.ping()\n26: - [ ] Verify method returns True when Docker is available\n27: - [ ] Verify method returns False when Docker is unavailable\n28: - [ ] Verify method handles DockerException gracefully\n29: - [ ] Verify method logs warning when Docker is unavailable\n30: - [ ] Verify method does not raise exceptions on failure\n31: \n32: **Verification**: Run unit test for check_docker_available with mocked client\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ### Task 3: Verify Docker client lazy initialization\n37: - [ ] Verify client property is implemented\n38: - [ ] Verify _client is initialized to None\n39: - [ ] Verify client property creates Docker client on first access\n40: - [ ] Verify client property uses docker.from_env()\n41: - [ ] Verify client property returns cached client on subsequent calls\n42: - [ ] Verify client property handles DockerException during initialization\n43: \n44: **Verification**: Run unit test for client property with mocked docker.from_env\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ### Task 4: Verify build_image method signature and structure\n49: - [ ] Verify build_image method accepts dockerfile_path: Path parameter\n50: - [ ] Verify build_image method accepts context_path: Path parameter\n51: - [ ] Verify build_image method accepts image_name: str parameter\n52: - [ ] Verify build_image method accepts tag: str parameter with default \"latest\"\n53: - [ ] Verify build_image method accepts build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] parameter\n54: - [ ] Verify return type is Dict[str, Any]\n55: - [ ] Verify method calls check_docker_available\n56: - [ ] Verify method raises RuntimeError when Docker is unavailable\n57: - [ ] Verify method constructs full_image_name correctly\n58: \n59: **Verification**: Review docker_service.py and verify method implementation matches design\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ### Task 5: Verify build_image method implementation\n64: - [ ] Verify method validates Docker availability before build\n65: - [ ] Verify method calls self.client.images.build with correct parameters\n66: - [ ] Verify build is called with path=str(context_path)\n67: - [ ] Verify build is called with dockerfile=str(dockerfile_path)\n68: - [ ] Verify build is called with tag=full_image_name\n69: - [ ] Verify build is called with buildargs=build_args if provided\n70: - [ ] Verify build is called with rm=True\n71: - [ ] Verify build is called with forcerm=True\n72: - [ ] Verify method calls get_image_info after successful build\n73: - [ ] Verify method adds build_time to returned dict\n74: - [ ] Verify method handles DockerException appropriately\n75: \n76: **Verification**: Run unit test for build_image with mocked Docker client\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ### Task 6: Verify build_image method error handling\n81: - [ ] Verify method raises RuntimeError when Docker is unavailable\n82: - [ ] Verify method raises RuntimeError when build fails\n83: - [ ] Verify error message includes original exception\n84: - [ ] Verify method logs build operation start\n85: - [ ] Verify method logs build failure if verbose\n86: \n87: **Verification**: Run unit tests for build_image error scenarios\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ### Task 7: Verify get_image_info method implementation\n92: - [ ] Verify get_image_info method accepts image_name: str parameter\n93: - [ ] Verify return type is Dict[str, Any]\n94: - [ ] Verify method calls self.client.images.get(image_name)\n95: - [ ] Verify method extracts image_id from attrs[\"Id\"]\n96: - [ ] Verify image_id is truncated to first 12 characters\n97: - [ ] Verify method extracts size from attrs[\"Size\"]\n98: - [ ] Verify method calls _format_size for size_bytes\n99: - [ ] Verify method returns dict with image_name, image_id, image_size, size_bytes\n100: - [ ] Verify method handles DockerException and returns empty dict\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 955. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装 Implementation Tasks\n\n**Module**: `cmd/cli`\n**Language**: Python\n**Size**: M\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Verify DockerService class structure and initialization\n- [ ] Verify DockerService class exists in agentcube/services/docker_service.py\n- [ ] Verify __init__ method with verbose parameter\n- [ ] Verify verbose flag is stored as instance variable\n- [ ] Verify logging configuration based on verbose flag\n- [ ] Verify lazy initialization of _client property\n- [ ] Verify class docstring describes functionality\n- [ ] Verify imports are correct (docker, logging, time, pathlib, typing)\n\n**Verification**: Run `python -c \"from agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService; s = DockerService(verbose=True); print(s)\"` and verify it instantiates correctly\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775871764852,"end":1775871764861}}}}
